description: This file sets up and runs an asynchronous task to compare responses from a regular agent and a reasoning agent, both using OpenAI models, to count the number of 'r's in the word 'strawberry'. It involves importing modules, creating agent instances, and executing asynchronous response printing with console formatting.

classes.name: Agent
classes.description: Represents an AI agent configured with a language model, capable of generating responses.

methods.name: main
methods.description: Asynchronous function that runs the main logic: displaying console rules and awaiting agent responses.
